<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-6925] BZip2Codec incorrectly implements read()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6925</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-4012&quot; title=&quot;Providing splitting support for bzip2 compressed files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-4012&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-4012&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added an implementation of read() in BZip2InputStream that doesn&apos;t work correctly when reading bytes &amp;gt; 0x80. This causes EOFExceptions when working with BZip2 compressed data inside of sequence files in some datasets.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12472420">HADOOP-6925</key>
            <summary>BZip2Codec incorrectly implements read()</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
