                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12902101" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 22:11:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch fixes the read() implementation to correctly mask with 0xff before upcasting to int. Also augments the unit test to check the single-byte read() function - the new test fails before this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902112" author="roelofs" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 22:29:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This may fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6852&quot; title=&quot;apparent bug in concatenated-bzip2 support (decoding)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6852&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6852&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, as well.  (The unit test in question is available as a standalone patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-1927&quot; title=&quot;unit test for HADOOP-6835 (concatenated gzip support)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAPREDUCE-1927&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAPREDUCE-1927&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is awaiting review.)  If so, I can update the unit test to uncomment the relevant bzip2 test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll make a note to check this soon...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902114" author="eli" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 22:30:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks good. Nice find.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902118" author="chris.douglas" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 22:32:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;sigh&lt;/b&gt; This was introduced between v9 of the patch and v11. Good catch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902125" author="eli" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 22:48:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk and branch-0.20.  Thanks Todd.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902127" author="eli" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 22:51:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Forgot to mention that I verified TestCodec passed on trunk and the merge to branch-0.21. Previous comment has a typo, meant &lt;b&gt;branch-0.21&lt;/b&gt; not branch-0.20.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902247" author="hudson" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 01:07:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Hadoop-Common-trunk-Commit #365 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Hadoop-Common-trunk-Commit/365/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Hadoop-Common-trunk-Commit/365/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6925&quot; title=&quot;BZip2Codec incorrectly implements read()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6925&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6925&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. BZip2Codec incorrectly implements read(). Contributed by Todd Lipcon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902267" author="roelofs" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 01:41:42 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This may fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6852&quot; title=&quot;apparent bug in concatenated-bzip2 support (decoding)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6852&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6852&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, as well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nope, concatenation is still broken.  Ah, well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902380" author="hudson" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 11:21:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Hadoop-Common-trunk #433 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Hadoop-Common-trunk/433/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Hadoop-Common-trunk/433/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
